screw_cold_spray(
    robot,
    length_mm=40,        # how far from “head” to hole along the travel
    amp_start_mm=8,      # big amplitude at the head
    amp_end_mm=1.5,      # tight near the hole
    pitch_mm=3.0,        # thread pitch (distance per cycle)
    steps_per_cycle=30,  # samples per cycle
    cycle_s=0.015,
    lookahead_s=0.2,
    gain=2500,
    tilt_start_deg=15,
    tilt_end_deg=8,
    axis="x",            # right→left is decreasing X in this setup
)



"Tuning notes
length_mm: set this to the distance from your “head start point” to the leak along the travel axis.

amp_start_mm / amp_end_mm: how wide the weave begins vs. ends. Amp_end_mm should be ≥ your spray footprint radius so the threads “pack” the center.

pitch_mm: smaller pitch = tighter thread spacing (more coverage).

steps_per_cycle: more samples per pitch if you see gaps.

axis: use "x" if right→left is –X in your TCP frame (as in my default). If your jig is rotated, switch to "y""
